The Full User Journey:
First-Time User (Never coded before):
Visit Hololand.com → Simpsons-style flythrough (30 seconds)
Land in Central Plaza → See the world, feel the vibe
NPC Guide appears: "Hey! Want a tour?"
Walk to Creator District → Enter your studio
Brittney greets you: "Ready to build your first world?"
Click 🎤 button: "Create a small tavern"
Watch it build in real-time → Done in 30 seconds
Brittney: "Want to add anything else?"
Keep building by voice until happy
Click "Publish" → Your world goes live
Return to Hub → Portal to your world appears
Experienced Creator:
Land in hub → Immediately walk/teleport to studio
Open HoloScript Editor → Code directly
Use Brittney for quick additions: "Add 5 NPCs"
Test in preview mode
Publish when ready
Social User (Not building, just exploring):
Land in hub → Walk to Social Hub
Enter "The Lounge" → Hang out with friends
Someone shares portal link → "Check out my D&D dungeon!"
Click portal → Instantly load into their world
Play their campaign → Never touch building tools
Why This is Better:
✅ Immersive from second 1 - You're IN the metaverse, not looking at a website

✅ Discoverable - Walking around reveals features naturally

✅ Social - See other creators, bump into people

✅ Flexible - Beginners use wizard, pros use code, everyone uses voice

✅ Feels like a place - Not a tool, but a world to inhabit

Technical Flow (Behind the Scenes):

User visits Hololand.com
  ↓
Load WebGL/Three.js scene (Holoverse hub)
  ↓
User walks to Studio building
  ↓
Open studio interface (React components load)
  ↓
User clicks "Talk to Brittney" button
  ↓
Microphone activates → Speech-to-text
  ↓
Send to Ollama (Brittney model)
  ↓
Generate HoloScript
  ↓
Compile to Three.js scene
  ↓
Update preview in real-time
  ↓
User clicks "Publish"
  ↓
Upload to Hololand marketplace
  ↓
Portal appears in Hub